                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Fragment on one block, seemingly recording a gift of gold fo the upkeep of a lamp. Possibly a fragment of one of the preserved incomplete inscriptions at the site, that is, the beginning of lines 4-6 of DHARMA_INSKotumpalur00008 <!--Update cross-ref-->(?), which is on the block continuous to the right. However, it is difficult to find a continuity between the end of line 4 of DHARMA_INSKotumpalur00008<!--Update cross-ref-->, of which the following lost portion is expected to be <foreign>ā viḷakku</foreign>, while this seems not warranted at the beginning of line 2 of the present fragment. Nonetheless, it is also conceivable that DHARMA_INSKotumpalur00008 <!--Update cross-ref--> and the present inscription are two block fragments of a inscription, of hich a third fragment block is lost.</summary>
                    </msContents>
